#. type: Title ##
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:284
#, no-wrap
msgid "Key Insights"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:288
msgid ""
"**Enumeration Efficiency**: The enumeration test (TEST_ENUM2000FILES) "
"performs only ~51 operations for 2000 files due to batching, making it the "
"most efficient operation per item."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:291
msgid ""
"**Read/Write Quantum Impact**: With 1MB quantum size, the 100MB file tests "
"perform only ~100 operations each, making them very efficient for bulk data "
"transfer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:294
msgid ""
"**Cache Validation Overhead**: The cache validation test performs the most "
"operations (30,000), making it ideal for stress testing and cache coherency "
"validation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4. '
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:297
msgid ""
"**Lock Operations**: The lock/unlock test provides a pure protocol overhead "
"measurement with 20,000 rapid operations that don't involve actual data "
"transfer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '5. '
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:300
msgid ""
"**Directory Operations**: Directory creation and traversal tests "
"(1,110-1,500 operations) provide good measurements for metadata operation "
"performance."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:306
msgid ""
"These operation counts help identify which tests are best suited for: - "
"**Protocol efficiency testing**: Enumeration, large file I/O - **Stress "
"testing**: Cache validation, lock/unlock, open/stat/read - **Metadata "
"performance**: Directory operations, cache hits - **Real-world simulation**: "
"Mixed operations, open/stat/read patterns"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:308
#, no-wrap
msgid "IO Monitoring (Developer mode)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:312
msgid ""
"The IO Monitoring capability is an advanted performance analysis mechanism "
"to enable Netatalk developers to validate performance enhancements and "
"quantify AFP-to-IO operation impact."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:315
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Requires afp_lantest to be run on the same (Linux) host as Netatalk, to enable access to the afpd processes disk\n"
"IO operation stats via the Linux proc virtual filesystem.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:318
msgid ""
"Distributions running systemd do not allow exiting /proc filesystem to be "
"remounted, therefore a secondary proc mount is required at /proc_io from the "
"default /proc location."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:322
msgid ""
"Example - Run as root to allow 'root' GID access to /proc_io for other UIDs "
"(When running afp_lantest as user other than root, update gid accordingly.): "
"`mkdir -p /proc_io && mount -t proc -o hidepid=0,gid=0 proc /proc_io`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:324
msgid ""
"NB; IO Monitoring is intended for use with the Netatalk test Docker "
"container (see `testsuite_alp.Dockerfile`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:328
msgid "Run all tests with default settings:"
msgstr "すべてのテストをデフォルト設定で実行する"

#. type: Plain text
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:330
#, no-wrap
msgid "    afp_lantest -h server.example.com -u testuser -w password -s TestVolume\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:332
msgid "Run only cache-focused tests:"
msgstr "キャッシュに重点を置いたテストのみを実行する"

#. type: Plain text
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:334
#, no-wrap
msgid "    afp_lantest -C -h server.example.com -u testuser -w password -s TestVolume\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:336
msgid "Run specific tests (file operations):"
msgstr "特定のテストを実行する（ファイル操作）"

#. type: Plain text
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:338
#, no-wrap
msgid "    afp_lantest -f 123 -h server.example.com -u testuser -w password -s TestVolume\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:340
msgid "Run tests optimized for gigabit network:"
msgstr "ギガビットネットワークに最適化されたテストを実行する"

#. type: Plain text
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:342
#, no-wrap
msgid "    afp_lantest -g -h server.example.com -u testuser -w password -s TestVolume\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: manpages/man1/afp_lantest.1.md:344
msgid "Run multiple iterations for statistical analysis:"
